      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ObjectDataSourceFilteringEventArgs" /> class is used to pass data to the <see cref="E:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ObjectDataSource.Filtering" /> event handler of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ObjectDataSource" /> control. The <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ObjectDataSourceFilteringEventArgs.ParameterValues" /> property provides access to the filter parameter values before the filtering operation is performed. You can cancel the <see cref="M:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ObjectDataSource.Select" /> method by setting the <see cref="P:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel" /> property of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ObjectDataSourceFilteringEventArgs" /> to true.</para>
    </remarks>
